  "market_context": "New York session open (08:30 EST) on October 30, 2023. Price initially rose to ~14450, then declined, sweeping the morning low near 14310.75, forming a consolidation range between ~14300–14350 before manipulating lower and distributing higher.",
  "key_observation": "After NY open, price swept the morning low (14310.75), formed a consolidation range, then executed a manipulation leg downward before reversing and distributing higher—classic AMD sequence on the 1-minute timeframe.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Identified NY open at 14350.00 and marked the morning low at 14310.75 as a liquidity target.",
    "Step 2: Observed price sweeping that low and forming a consolidation range (green box) between ~14300–14350.",
    "Step 3: Noted aggressive downward displacement (manipulation) out of the range, sweeping the low again and closing back into the range.",
    "Step 4: Looked for long entries using either an inversion of the manipulated low or a box setup using the prior body’s low (~14334.75).",
    "Step 5: Planned entry on retest of the inversion/box level with stop below the sweep low and 2R target upward."
  ],
  "outcome": null,
  "lessons": "On LTF, AMD manifests as sweep → consolidation → manipulation → distribution; valid long entries require inversion or box setup after manipulation, not premature market structure shift attempts.",
